         <div type="poem"
              xml:id="txt_GrayTh1716_epmc"
              corresp="authors.xml#txt_GrayTh1716_epmc"
              subtype="eceptext"
              rendition="#lgvspace"
              rhyme="aa"
              met="-+|-+|-+|-+/"
              n="8"
              ana="#iamb #tetrameter #couplet">
            <link type="author" target="authors.xml#aut_GrayTh1716"/>
            <head>[Epitaph on Mrs Clerke]</head>
            <lg>
               <l n="1">Lo! where this silent marble weeps,</l>
               <l n="2">A friend, a wife, a mother sleeps:</l>
               <l n="3">A heart, within whose sacred cell</l>
               <l n="4">The peaceful virtues loved to dwell.</l>
               <l n="5">Affection warm, and faith sincere,</l>
               <l n="6">And soft humanity were there.</l>
               <l n="7">In agony, in death, resigned,</l>
               <l n="8">She felt the wound she left behind.</l>
               <l n="9">Her infant image, here below,</l>
               <l n="10">Sits smiling on a father's woe:</l>
               <l n="11">Whom what awaits, while yet he strays</l>
               <l n="12">Along the lonely vale of days?</l>
               <l n="13">A pang, to secret sorrow dear;</l>
               <l n="14">A sigh; an unavailing tear;</l>
               <l n="15">Till time shall every grief remove,</l>
               <l n="16">With life, with memory, and with love.</l>
            </lg>
         </div>
